	abstract = {One of the continuing challenges for Cognitive Systems Engineering (CSE) is the need to develop a deeper understanding of how cognitive tools influence operator performance, consistent with one of the fundamental precepts of CSE that “automation does not simply supplant human activity but rather changes it, often in ways unintended and unanticipated by the designers of automation”. Equally important is the need for CSE as a field to influence the design decisions of system developers.
